docs.text: when i originally saw the trailer for " analyze this " a few months ago , i must admit , i thought it looked kind of lame .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and then when the commercials started popping up a week or two ago , i thought it looked outright bad .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but then when " analyze this " finally opened a few days ago , an odd thing happened .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it got great reviews .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: critics were proclaiming it " hilarious " and a " dead-on parody of mob movies " .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: well , with praise like that , i figured , it must be good and so i headed off to the theater .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: you know that expression that says always trust your gut instincts ?
docs.label: negative

docs.text: well , turns out that expression is more valid than i ever gave it credit for .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: " analyze this " is slow , unfunny , and badly acted .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: don't get me wrong , i think that deniro is one of the top ten greatest actors of the century , but he is just out of his league here .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: i think the problem is he didn't quite know how to approach this material .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: he plays his character , mob boss paull vitti , somewhere in between the realm of comedy and drama .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: if he had played the character straight , along the lines of leslie nielson in the " naked gun " series , he probably would have been a lot more successful .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: as it is , though , he plays the character completely serious at some moments , and for laughs at others .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: this doesn't work .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it creates an uneven character that never breaks out of the deniro mold ; you always know it's him .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and the movie is badly paced , too .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it never takes off .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it just crawls from one scene to another without any forward momentum .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: i think the blame for this should be placed on the script .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it's obvious the writer had a good idea for a movie , mob boss faces breakdown and needs the services of a psychiatrist , but once this is established , the movie doesn't really go anywhere .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the formula of the film seems to be this : billy crystal says no to deniro , deniro forces him , and much wackiness ensues .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: this formula of sorts is repeated several times throughout the movie .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: i've said it before and i'll say it again : the only thing that matters to me in a comedy is whether or not it's funny .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: if " analyze this " had been funny , the pacing and bad acting wouldn't have bothered me .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: i would have been too busy laughing to notice .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but as it is , i only chuckled a few times .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the only really funny scene is a dead-on parody of " the godfather " .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: sadly , though , i don't think anyone in the audience i saw it with realized it was a parody , because i was the only one laughing .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but my sense of humour , i have come to realize , is vastly different from the general population .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: i loathed " there's something about mary " , yet loved " baseketball " .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: now , if you want a movie that * i * think is funny , go out and see " office space " .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it's full of genuine laughs and won't leave you glancing at your watch every 10 minutes , as " analyze this " did .
docs.label: negative
